<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-812] Allow ConfusionMatrix to be Writable (via MatrixWritable)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-812</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ConfusionMatrix does not support Writable. This patch adds that feature. ConfusionMatrix is a subclass of MatrixWritable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since ConfusionMatrix is somewhat less than useful without the row/column labels, and MatrixWritable does not support writing bindings (it only saves numbers), this patch fixes both.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Includes unit test for ConfusionMatrix (previously missing) which includes exercise of MatrixWritable support for numbers and labels. (There is no independent unit test for MatrixWritable.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
